# April_Burton_Unit42_Assignment
Unit 42 code:you Cybersecurity Pathway Top Hat first assignment


SOC Incident Report: Case2025
Priority: High | Status: Investigated | 
Analyst: April D. Burton


  Executed Overview
   On January 22, 2025 at approximately 18:37 UTC, a workstation on the internal LAN (10.1,17,215) was compromised via a Social Engineering Attack/ A fake software vector.
   The user attempted to download, what was thought to be, "Google Authenticator", but was redirected to to a "Typos Quaded Domine", and upon execution of the malicious downloaded payload, the hostr was able to establish a persistent communication with a known malicious "Command & Control" (C2) infrastructer.
   Internal reconnaissance by the malware was noted. Through the primary activity remains focused on data exfilteration & maintaining a backdoor.  Folowing the download the system initiated the C2 traffic to multiple external ip addresses.
    
  The infected Host identification:
(The following internal assets were identified as the primary point of infection)
      Attribute                 Discovery Data
    User Account                 shutchenson0
     Host Name                  DESKTOP-L8C5GSJ
 Internal IP Address             10.1.17.215
Physical (MAC) address        00:d0:b7:26:4a:74

  Attack Vector & Threat Indicators
The infection chain began when the user visited the fraudulent website
designed to mimic an official software distribution.
   The access domain:
  *) authenticator.org
  *) google-authenticator.burlesson-appliance.net
   
  Malicious Activity:
The site delivereed a payload that desguised itself as a trusted
 security utility tool.
    
